ed processes of meaning and power, which have found heterogeneous historical elaborations over the past five centuries. Bringing together past and present, theory and narrative, it sows the historical, ethnographic and methodological deep into its critical procedures, offering an innovative understanding of cultural identities and imaginatively exploring the relationship between history and anthropology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, Modern. 0aSpacexSocial aspects. 0aTimexSocial aspects. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aIndian subcontinent.  aantinomian articulations.  acontingent entanglements.  amodern enticements.  amodernity.  apolitical philosophy.  asocial-political theory.  asocio-spatial/disciplinary subjects.  aspatial/temporal templates.  atime-space articulations.1 aDube, Saurabh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526105134zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526105134/original  a978-3-11-128281-7 Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA